    "description": "<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">During a conflict, you may use an action and spend <strong>@LOSS[5 mp]</strong> to choose another creature that can hear and understand you. That creature recovers </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>【</strong></span><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><strong>SL × 5</strong></span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>】 </strong></span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Hit Points and chooses </span><strong>@EFFECT[dex-up]</strong>, <strong>@EFFECT[ins-up]</strong>, <strong>@EFFECT[mig-up]</strong>, or <strong>@EFFECT[wlp-up]</strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\">: they treat the chosen Attribute as being one die size higher (up to a maximum of </span><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><strong>d12</strong></span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">) until the start of your next turn.</span> </p><hr /><p>Skill Level <strong>1</strong> - <strong>@GAIN[5 hp]</strong></p><p>Skill Level <strong>2</strong> - <strong>@GAIN[10 hp]</strong></p><p>Skill Level <strong>3</strong> - <strong>@GAIN[15 hp]</strong></p><p>Skill Level <strong>4</strong> - <strong>@GAIN[20 hp]</strong></p><p>Skill Level <strong>5</strong> - <strong>@GAIN[25 hp]</strong></p><p>Skill Level <strong>6</strong> - <strong>@GAIN[30 hp]</strong></p>",
